VERSION 1
WHEN PRESENT (?i)\bINSERT INTO\s+[^\s]+\s+\(.*=.*\$.*
WHEN EXPR MISSING:(SqlParameter|AddWithValue|Parameters\.Add|Parameters\.AddWithValue)
REPORT AS area_of_interest
REASON Detects INSERT statements with direct use of user input, which can lead to SQL injection.
TRACE Externalized rule logic for SQL Query: Non-parameterized INSERT Statements.
